<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-24T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-24T16:00:00-05:00" n="231" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d231">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/740a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-24T16:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 24, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1864. For your information. In reply to an inquiry as to whether we would
                            join with the Allies in an agreement not to recognize independently any
                            new Russian Government, the Department has informed the French
                            Ambassador that we would be glad to exchange views with the Allies at
                            any time on the subject but that we would not bind ourselves to a course
                            which might look to Russia as a measure of compulsion.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>